					<p>In 1997, Evander Holyfield was on top of the boxing world, having already knocked Mike Tyson out cold in their original meeting.</p><p>What he didn't realize: Tyson was on his way down and out with revenge on the brain for Holyfield. Evander agreed to fight Tyson again, and perhaps pride got in the way of better logic.</p><p>Tyson, disgruntled with slowly losing to Holyfield again, resorted to biting Holyfield's ears while removing a piece of one ear.</p><p>The fight was immediately ended by Mills Lane after the second bite, signaling the start of a meltdown for Tyson, and he's never recovered.</p>
