				<div class="slide-description">
					
						
										
					<p>The third overall pick of the 1989 NFL Draft had a stellar career at Oklahoma State, and picked up right where he left off in the NFL.</p><p>Considered one of the best running backs in professional history, Sanders would retire at the age of 31, citing the losing style of play in Detroit as too much to bear.&nbsp;</p><p>In an ugly lawsuit by the Lions, the judge ruled Sanders didn't uphold his end of the contract he was under when he retired, and Barry was forced to pay back millions to the Lions.</p><p>He was gone too soon, and Lions fans have never been the same.</p>
