					<div class="slide-title">
						<h2>48. Babe Ruth Ends 1926 World Series by Getting Caught Stealing Second Base</h2>
						
					</div>
								
				<div class="slide-image">
					
						
							<img alt="250px-ruth1926-3_display_image" rel="original_file_name:250px-Ruth1926-3.jpg" src="http://cdn.bleacherreport.net/images_root/slides/photos/000/495/874/250px-Ruth1926-3_display_image.jpg?1289382625" />						
					
					
					<br>
					
					
					
					<small class="photo-credit"></small>
				</div>
				
				<div class="slide-description">
					
						
										
					<p>Babe Ruth was quoted as saying he thought the Cardinals would be caught off guard with him trying to steal second in the ninth inning of Game 7 of the 1926 World Series.</p><p>With two outs, Ruth bolted for second but was thrown out by a mile, ending the series and handing the Cardinals the title.</p><p>The 1926 World Series is the only one to end on a player caught stealing to this day.</p>
